28/03/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turks headed to the polls on Sunday (28 March) to elect approximately 93,000 local assembly representatives.
There are 43.5 million registered voters in Turkey.
Recent polls give the ruling Justice and Development Party a substantial edge over its rivals.
It is expected to keep control of major cities, including Ankara and Istanbul.
In other news, an earthquake measuring 5.3 on the Richter scale hit the province of Erzurum on Sunday.
Local officials reported that at least six people were injured.
A quake in the same area killed 10 people on Thursday and was followed by more than 100 aftershocks.
(AP, AFP, Anadolu Agency - 28/03/04)
